text: Serena Deeb (born June 29, 1986) is an American professional wrestler currently signed to All Elite Wrestling (AEW). She is best known for wrestling with World Wrestling Entertainment on their SmackDown brand under the ring name, Serena, where she was part of CM Punk's wrestling stable Straight Edge Society. While part of Ohio Valley Wrestling, Serena was won the OVW Women's Championship six times and was named Queen of FCW one time while part of Florida Championship Wrestling. Serena was released from her WWE contract for not portraying her Straight Edge Society gimmick in real life, but because SmackDown was pre-recorded, her release was not revealed immediately, and gave her one last appearance on WWE programming which aired on August 27, 2010. She returned in 2017 to compete in the Mae Young Classic. She then became a coach at the Performance Center in Orlando, Florida. She was released for a second time on April 15, 2020, and joined AEW that September.
